OL,3,CZambia running dry: What do rich
OL,4,Cnations owe countries on the climate
OL,5,Cfrontline?
OL,7,FIn the busy capital of Lusaka, the
OL,8,Feffects of the power outages are
OL,9,Fobvious. Those with private solar
OL,10,Fpanels or diesel generators power
OL,11,Ftheir homes and businesses at extra
OL,12,Fcost.
OL,14,FOthers crowd into malls, where huge
OL,15,Fbackup generators keep the power on,
OL,16,Fgathering in cafes to plug their
OL,17,Flaptops in for work.
OL,19,FIn shopping centre corridors, any
OL,20,Fpower socket on the wall has someone's
OL,21,Fmobile phone plugged in for charging.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/16
