OL,7,FHe has invested in rechargeable
OL,8,Fshavers but can no longer use other
OL,9,Ftools like his plug-in hairdryer. His
OL,10,Ftakings are down 85%.
OL,12,FJust down the road, Karen Bowa runs a
OL,13,Fbutcher's shop.
OL,15,FShe usually has two freezers full of
OL,16,Fmeat but without power, she has had to
OL,17,Freduce the amount of meat she buys and
OL,18,Fstore it in just one of the freezers
OL,19,Fusing big ice blocks to keep it cold.
