OL,3,CZambia running dry: What do rich
OL,4,Cnations owe countries on the climate
OL,5,Cfrontline?
OL,7,FWorld Vision spokesperson Agatha Mali
OL,8,Fsays it is frustrating to see the
OL,9,Fimpact of power outages impacting
OL,10,Fpeople's lives and livelihoods.
OL,12,F"Business gets slow, activities go
OL,13,Fdown, most shops are closed - most
OL,14,Fcompanies rely on power, so even if
OL,15,Fthey have generators or alternative
OL,16,Fpower sources, it's not enough to
OL,17,Fsustain them or enable them to do
OL,18,Ftheir work accordingly," she says.
